content:
Posting Data to the Application Object using the Post to Object Action

You can submit an OmniScript directly to the Vlocity Application object using the Post to Object Action Element. The Vlocity Application object enables an in-progress OmniScript to be stored and resumed later.

When a user submits for the first time, OmniScript:

Creates an Application record with a name equal to the postNameTemplate property.
Populates the Full JSON, Data JSON, and Files Map fields.
Processes root level files and adds them as attachments to the application record.
Sets the Application Status to Submitted.

The Post to Object Action Element is only available in Communities and Salesforce Sites. 

To post data to the Vlocity application object:

Create a Post to Object Action element by following the steps in Creating an Auto Number Field and Configuring a Workflow Rule.
Modify the Application page layout to include the Review button and ApplicationDataJSONPage Visualforce section, as described in Reviewing or Modifying a Submitted OmniScript.
title: Posting Data to Vlocity Application Object with OmniScript
